text: Is this going to be like Accession? ie; they aren't really on an actual spaceship. It's just a test to see how two people would react to finding themselves awake and alone on a giant starship years from anywhere?  The other thing is of course that if it was a hibernation ship on a 120 year journey to another star system why would all the life support be up and running when they are "accidentally awoken". Still only having to wait 9 years isn't so bad. (Or is it 90? I can't make it out).  One of my favorite giant spaceship cruising between the stars stories is a short story from the 1950s(?). Clans and tribes have established themselves. People fight over food and supplies. A few try to solve the mystery that is their predicament. At the end we find out the truth as you only can in a written story. The "people" are actually intelligent rats that have infested a starship and the real crew are about to open the door and flush them all out into space ....

text: I really don't know why people are saying that they've included the 'whole film in the trailer' and that they've 'spoilt' it. I can tell you, I've read Jon Spaihts' (amazing) script and the trailer doesn't spoil anything. I was surprised of a few things that happened in the script and none of those surprises are in this trailer. This trailer simply shows you that two people have woken up on a spaceship and they soon fall in love. Sure, there's going to be action, it's set in space, it'd be really boring if it just focused on Jennifer and Chris' characters.  Can't we just be happy that, in the midst of all the remakes & sequels we've had this year (far too many to count), we're getting a film that is fresh and original. It's not like Wall-E, it's not like 'Titanic in space' and it's not like Gravity. Just because they feature romance and it's a sci-fi doesn't mean it's going to be unlike any other film we've already seen.  Who cares if you don't like Jennifer Lawrence or Chris Pratt? In my opinion, I find Pratt to be annoying but that won't stop me watching this film as I've been looking forward to it for the past year.  See the film, don't see the film, it's up to you. Please don't moan that it's spoilt everything because it hasn't, I promise you. It's impossible to include the whole film (90-120mins long) in 2min26sec long trailer. Be realistic.

text: This movie inspires a lot of thought of space and time and how we all are compartmentalized.¬† Without giving away any spoilers of the movie I would like to say this movie inspires basic instincts and reveals a lot of sad truths.¬† Compartmentalization happens with the rich and poor and left and right.¬† Go too far to the left or right you become locked in a political wrestling match continually looking for a fight and reason to demonize each other.¬† Rich want to get rid of the poor and the not so wealthy want revolution and excuse to take property they think they are entitled to.¬† Wonder neutral or middle ground¬† and you become irrelevant.¬† In reality we live in a great civilization that had its moment and is in a free fall at the moment.¬†   ¬†¬†¬† This movie shows how you can pull people into your world and either create enemies for them to fight the rest of their life or teach them to be neutral balanced and be irrelevant.¬† We are compartmentalized by computers that search out our favorites and your knowledge becomes specialized and tailored to fit.¬† You rarely see things from the random perspective of the old fashion television news that tailored the audience to who ever owned the station.¬† I am not saying there is right and left or rich or poor in this movie, I am just¬†just inspired by a very interesting storyline.¬†   ¬†¬† Just the same as this movie you have to decide the narrative or you will be dragged into a world where you do not understand fully and when you do figure it out you become irrelevant and forgotten even though you could of helped this fallen civilization.¬† I hope there is a sequel to¬†this story it absolutely needs a second time around because it is a spark in the right direction....
